description: From trammel (“fishing net; shackle”), from Old French tramail (“net for catching fishes”), from Late Latin tremaculum.

adjectives.description: untrammeled (comparative more untrammeled, superlative most untrammeled)

entries.meaning: Not limited or restricted; unrestrained; limitless.
examples: A system of untrammeled discretion exists when there are no limits on what officials may consider in reaching a decision [..]
